snippet.textDisplay: It’s definitely an odd feeling. Lots of emotions. Both my roommate and his girlfriend are at home due to work being shut down. Yet I’m still required to go to work in the same town. You get upset but then you realize you should be lucky you haven’t gotten laid off or work postponed with no pay. But as it goes on and on you wake up every morning with the people around you sleeping in and doing their own thing for a week or two now and it just gets harder and harder to WANT to go to work. Then work rolls out a work from home program but it’s VERY slow moving. So you start to complain again. Then you realize once again that you should feel lucky that this is even an option to begin with. So it’s a rollercoaster of emotions right now. Very crazy.
